       Infrared Spectromicroscopy and Future Infrared Sources Workshop
                      2001 ALS Users' Meeting Workshop
                            October 16 & 17, 2001

   Scope: This workshop will have two parts: Day 1 will be devoted to
   sharing IR spectromicroscopy results done at the ALS and to infrared
   spectromicroscopy applications in general. In day 2 we will discuss
   ideas for building a dedicated infrared ring at the ALS and more
   importantly the science that will drive such a facility.

   Summary: ALS Infrared Spectromicroscopy and Future Infrared Sources
   Workshop, Synchrotron Radiation News 15(1), 10-11 (2002).

   Program: Workshop Program.

   Location: LBNL, Building 50A Auditorium Directions to LBNL.

